Basic Commands------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git init 	 	// Initialize local git repository.

$ git add <file> 	// Add File(s) to index. To add all files use the '.' as a "file name".

$ git status		// Check status of working tree.

$ git commit 		// Commit changes in index.

$ git commit -m 'commit msg..'	// Do a commit and add a message in the command line.

$ git push 		// Push to remote repository.

$ git pull		// Pull latest from remote repository.

$ git clone 		// Clone repository into new directory.

$ git rm --cached <file>	// If a file has added using 'git add' and we want to remove it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------






Installation--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ sudo apt-get install git

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------








Global configuration------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

// Example: change the git editor to vim.
$ git --global core.editor "vim"		// Also $ export GIT_EDITOR=vim will do the trick.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------









Gitignore file------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a file where we tell git which files we want him to ignore.
This file need to be created manually.

To ignore a file we write the name of the file within the .gitignore file.
We can also add a all folder to the .gitignore file by writing the folder path.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------








Branches------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git branch <name>		// Create a new branch.


